[PATCH] Enable gperftools tcmalloc for FRR daemons

From: StormLiangMS <stormliang@microsoft.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2026 05:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Enable gperftools tcmalloc for FRR daemons

Enable tcmalloc via --enable-gperf-tcmalloc configure flag so that FRR
links against libtcmalloc and activates the periodic memory release timer
(MallocExtension_ReleaseToSystem). This reduces memory fragmentation and
returns freed memory to the OS.

Reference: FRRouting/frr#19377

Signed-off-by: StormLiangMS <stormliang@microsoft.com>
---
 debian/rules |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
index 41b6c9f57..b8e3a1c00 100755
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -73,6 +73,7 @@ override_dh_auto_configure:
 		--disable-protobuf \
 		--disable-zeromq \
 		--enable-ospfapi \
+		--enable-gperf-tcmalloc \
 		--enable-multipath=514 \
 		--enable-pcre2posix \
 		\
